;The origins of Lightbeam
Permulaan Lightbeam


;Lightbeam began in July 2011 as Collusion, a personal project by Mozilla software developer <a href="%s">Atul Varma</a>.
Lightbeam bermula pada Julai 2011 sebagai Collusion, satu projek peribadi oleh pembangun perisian Mozilla <a href="%s">Atul Varma</a>.


;Inspired by the book, <em>The Filter Bubble</em>, Atul created an experimental add-on to visualize browsing behavior and data collection on the Web.
Diinspirasikan menurut peraturan, <em>The Filter Bubble</em>, Atul mewujudkan satu tambahan percubaan membayangkan melayari tingkah laku dan pengumpulan data di Jaringan.


;In February 2012, Gary Kovacs, Mozilla CEO at the time, introduced the Collusion add-on in a <a href="%s">TED talk</a> (now one of the most watched TED talks of all time) about exposing online tracking.
Pada Februari 2012, Gary Kovacs, Mozilla CEO pada masa itu, memperkenalkan addon Collusion di dalam <a href="%s"> ucapan TEDnya</a> (sekarang satu daripada perbincangan TED paling banyak ditonton semua masa) tentang mendedahkan penjejakan dalam talian.


;In September 2012, Mozilla joined forces with faculty and student researchers at <a href="%s">Emily Carr University of Art + Design</a> to develop and implement visualizations for the add-on.
Pada September 2012, Mozilla bergabung bersama dengan pelajar penyelidikan di <a href="%s">Universiti Emily Carr daripada Art + Design</a> untuk membangunkan dan melaksanakan visualisasi untuk add-on.


;With the support of the Ford Foundation and the Natural Sciences and Engineering Research Council (NSERC), Collusion has been re-imagined as Lightbeam and was launched in the fall of 2013.
Dengan sokongan daripada Ford Foundation, Natural Sciences dan Majlis Penyelidikan Kejuruteraan (NSERC), Pakatan sulit telah membayangkan semula Lightbeam dan telah dilancarkan pada musim gugur 2013.


